It's not Sanjay's fault, but
he could never look like that.

717
01:10:57,679 --> 01:10:59,728
You are stunning.

718
01:11:07,338 --> 01:11:09,862
- What?
- It's yours.

719
01:11:13,224 --> 01:11:14,713
Thank you.

720
01:11:42,377 --> 01:11:45,738
<i>Hold me back!</i>

721
01:11:48,078 --> 01:11:53,425
<i>Make sure tonight you don't miss the finale of
"The Best of the West" curry competition,</i>

722
01:11:53,642 --> 01:11:56,560
<i>going out live on "Korma TV".</i>

723
01:12:01,168 --> 01:12:05,472
Look at this. Please, stand up.
Let's have a look.

724
01:12:07,651 --> 01:12:12,007
I had forgotten how
beautiful these are.

725
01:12:12,664 --> 01:12:14,805
I'd completely forgotten.

726
01:12:15,043 --> 01:12:16,484
I hadn't.

727
01:12:23,783 --> 01:12:27,680
- So, have you decided yet?
- No, she hasn't.

728
01:12:27,680 --> 01:12:29,727
It's gotta be special.

729
01:12:29,971 --> 01:12:32,073
We don't have much time.
The clock's ticking.

730
01:12:32,073 --> 01:12:37,012
Maybe we could just pick up a few fish suppers
on the way and curry them when we get there?!!

731
01:12:37,745 --> 01:12:42,022
- Do haggis for curries?!!
- Tender baby lamb...

732
01:12:42,592 --> 01:12:45,825
simmered in a  ginger
and garam masala,

733
01:12:46,362 --> 01:12:50,320
followed by "pomigrani" chicken
with rose petals.

734
01:12:50,320 --> 01:12:55,155
- And a light ginger sherbet for desert.
- Your wedding banquet!

735
01:12:55,531 --> 01:12:58,861
Of course. That's what he'd want.

736
01:12:59,282 --> 01:13:01,479
And maybe, chicken xacuti?

737
01:13:01,837 --> 01:13:05,109
"Best chicken xacuti this side of Maryhill."

738
01:13:12,423 --> 01:13:15,479
- Bobbi, where is he?
- He'll be here, I promise.

739
01:13:16,285 --> 01:13:18,483
We're still inside, Kary.

740
01:13:19,309 --> 01:13:22,875
I'm sorry I'm late.
Got a flat tire...

741
01:13:22,875 --> 01:13:24,447
Where's Priya?

742
01:14:01,336 --> 01:14:04,600
Not every family do get to have
a champion dancer.

743
01:14:04,600 --> 01:14:06,870
I'm glad you kept on going.

744
01:14:07,135 --> 01:14:08,515
Come.

745
01:14:09,216 --> 01:14:10,925
Oh, what the hell...

746
01:14:13,200 --> 01:14:15,609
There's something I need to tell you, ma'.

747
01:14:19,863 --> 01:14:21,356
I'm married.

748
01:14:26,300 --> 01:14:28,774
Her name's Janice, and
I pure love her.

749
01:14:34,745 --> 01:14:36,067
Well...

750
01:14:37,764 --> 01:14:40,549
It seems I have a lot to
learn about love.

751
01:14:48,245 --> 01:14:51,883
My children seem to understand it
much better than I do.

752
01:14:55,220 --> 01:14:57,224
Any more bombshells?

753
01:15:05,472 --> 01:15:09,600
Come on, let's go. We're gonna be late.
I don't wanna miss being on the telly.

754
01:15:09,600 --> 01:15:11,113
Let's go.

755
01:15:30,848 --> 01:15:32,469
It's right here.

756
01:15:38,455 --> 01:15:40,590
1, 2, 3.

757
01:15:40,590 --> 01:15:43,559
Chicken xacuti!

758
01:15:51,387 --> 01:15:53,908
You're looking wonderful.

759
01:15:57,008 --> 01:15:59,967
Well I hope you're firing on
all cylinders tonight, Sanjay.

760
01:15:59,967 --> 01:16:02,850
Nina's cooking a wedding
banquet fit for a king.

761
01:16:02,850 --> 01:16:05,268
That's just what I want to hear.

762
01:16:05,538 --> 01:16:06,938
We should go?

763
01:16:15,706 --> 01:16:18,712
<i>5, 4, 3, 2.</i>

764
01:16:23,616 --> 01:16:28,154
<i>Good evening, Scotland
and Mumbai!</i>

765
01:16:28,154 --> 01:16:32,891
<i>And welcome to this final of
"The Best of the West".</i>

766
01:16:34,208 --> 01:16:36,861
<i>We've got quite a feast to
serve up tonight</i>

767
01:16:36,861 --> 01:16:41,671
<i>and I sincerely hope you have will the
stomach to make it to the final course!</i>

768
01:16:41,998 --> 01:16:44,692
<i>Hold me back!
Hold me back!</i>

769
01:16:45,917 --> 01:16:48,401
<i>And in the blue zone...</i>

770
01:16:52,927 --> 01:16:55,132
<i>"The Bengal Tiger" from Bearsden.</i>

771
01:17:04,326 --> 01:17:06,713
Mum, this is Janice.

772
01:17:06,713 --> 01:17:10,480
Don't be angry with him, Miss Shah.
It was all my idea.

773
01:17:10,480 --> 01:17:11,684
I pure love him.

774
01:17:11,880 --> 01:17:13,684
<i>- And in the yellow zone...</i>

775
01:17:14,684 --> 01:17:15,046
Good.

776
01:17:16,956 --> 01:17:18,279
Good.

777
01:17:18,599 --> 01:17:24,140
<i>...are going to entice us with a spicy chicken roll,
flavoured with mixed indian pickles,</i>

778
01:17:24,140 --> 01:17:26,139
<i>stuffed with fresh garden spinache.</i>

779
01:17:26,434 --> 01:17:30,739
<i>And in the green zone...</i>

780
01:17:31,042 --> 01:17:34,600
<i>Sanjay Kahnna
of the "Jewel in the Crown".</i>

781
01:17:34,600 --> 01:17:38,105
<i>Sanjay has promised us the
Maharaja's banquet.</i>

782
01:17:38,105 --> 01:17:43,630
<i>His speciality being lamb
smoked with cloves and cinnamon.</i>

783
01:17:43,630 --> 01:17:49,770
<i>A taste that promises to melt
our hearts and light our fire.</i>

784
01:17:50,158 --> 01:17:53,803
<i>- Hold me back!
- Hold me back!</i>

785
01:17:54,410 --> 01:17:56,781
<i>And in the orange zone...</i>

786
01:17:57,855 --> 01:18:00,878
<i>The Shah of "The New Taj".</i>

787
01:18:00,878 --> 01:18:03,800
<i>Inspired by the whispering
palaces of Jaipur,</i>

788
01:18:04,333 --> 01:18:08,539
<i>Nina Shah has prepared a wedding
banquet fit for queens.</i>

789
01:18:08,793 --> 01:18:13,720
<i>Will she entice the judges with
the tender baby lamb chops?</i>

790
01:18:13,720 --> 01:18:18,733
<i>So, ladies and gentlemen,
let the battle commence.</i>

791
01:19:13,645 --> 01:19:15,709
That'll never happen, you know.

792
01:19:15,956 --> 01:19:19,325
- The two of you. Not like that.
- Like what, Sanjay?

793
01:19:20,449 --> 01:19:22,341
Come on, her mother will
never allow it.

794
01:19:24,153 --> 01:19:26,480
She won't run away again.
D'you know why?

795
01:19:26,480 --> 01:19:28,806
Because this time she's got
something to stay for.

796
01:19:29,042 --> 01:19:32,273
I won't be too sure about that.
She's not gonna risk it.

797
01:19:32,273 --> 01:19:34,259
She'd lose everything.

798
01:19:34,259 --> 01:19:37,235
D'you really think she wants
to lose her family again?

799
01:19:37,235 --> 01:19:39,080
Even for love?

800
01:19:39,635 --> 01:19:42,112
Chances of that are piss and pooh.

801
01:19:46,259 --> 01:19:49,165
That's lovely.
Fit for a king.

802
01:19:53,055 --> 01:19:55,532
OK, stole the lemon.
Here we go.

803
01:19:59,104 --> 01:20:01,842
<i>20 minutes of cooking time remaining.</i>

804
01:20:09,035 --> 01:20:10,266
What?

805
01:20:14,506 --> 01:20:15,900
Kiss me.

806
01:20:20,166 --> 01:20:22,349
We're on national television...

807
01:20:22,655 --> 01:20:24,324
We are.

808
01:20:38,863 --> 01:20:42,320
<i>Hold me back. What's going on
in the orange zone?</i>

809
01:20:42,320 --> 01:20:45,773
<i>She must have forgotten some
very crucial spices.</i>

810
01:20:52,457 --> 01:20:54,300
<i>Oh, dear, there goes another one.</i>

811
01:21:12,402 --> 01:21:13,729
Nina.

812
01:21:19,799 --> 01:21:21,762
She's gone, ma'.

813
01:21:22,226 --> 01:21:24,440
Then why are you still here?

814
01:21:27,261 --> 01:21:29,842
Don't make the same mistake I did.

815
01:21:30,046 --> 01:21:33,480
I loved your dad but I always knew...

816
01:21:34,138 --> 01:21:36,678
in my heart of heart of hearts,

817
01:21:37,628 --> 01:21:39,615
he wasn't the one.

818
01:21:42,339 --> 01:21:43,675
Raj?

819
01:21:46,617 --> 01:21:48,854
Trophies don't matter.

820
01:21:49,205 --> 01:21:52,229
The only thing that matters is love.

821
01:22:00,455 --> 01:22:02,688
Go on, hurry up.

822
01:22:02,937 --> 01:22:05,691
And don't you let that girl
out of your sight again.

823
01:22:56,603 --> 01:23:00,394
<i>Welcome back, girls. I hope
you've got your mangoes.</i>

824
01:23:03,473 --> 01:23:04,632
Oh, hold me back,

825
01:23:04,667 --> 01:23:08,265
<i>that was a narrow escape for
the "Taj" ladies, let me tell you!</i>

826
01:23:09,221 --> 01:23:13,142
<i>Right, you've got 30 seconds so let's
get your finishing touches on that.</i>

827
01:23:13,142 --> 01:23:16,350
<i>You don't have to cook the pickles,
you can buy that in a shop. Come on then!</i>

828
01:23:16,350 --> 01:23:19,050
<i>Come on, get going, get going!</i>

829
01:23:19,050 --> 01:23:23,676
<i>Right, you got 10, 9, 8, 7,</i>

830
01:23:24,020 --> 01:23:29,492
<i>6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1.</i>

831
01:23:29,565 --> 01:23:32,409
<i>Hold me back!</i>

832
01:23:33,000 --> 01:23:35,639
<i>All our contestants have
worked hard and</i>

833
01:23:35,639 --> 01:23:38,299
<i>have been very ambitious with their dishes.</i>

834
01:23:38,696 --> 01:23:44,511
<i>"Korma TV" is proud to have Scotland's
top chefs as our judges today.</i>

835
01:23:44,879 --> 01:23:48,371
<i>They take their duties very seriously.</i>

836
01:23:52,394 --> 01:23:55,848
<i>The smells in the studio are divine.</i>

837
01:24:02,106 --> 01:24:06,827
<i>4 contestants, 4 judges and
4 outstanding dishes.</i>

838
01:24:07,464 --> 01:24:11,226
<i>A close call between "The Jewel"
and "The New Taj", let me tell ya.</i>

839
01:24:11,908 --> 01:24:16,175
<i>Nina Shah's mogul menu was
beautifully prepared</i>

840
01:24:16,175 --> 01:24:21,826
<i>with each and every one of the delicate
flavours complementing each other perfectly.</i>

841
01:24:21,826 --> 01:24:25,391
<i>But Sanjay Kahnna confounded our senses</i>

842
01:24:25,391 --> 01:24:29,013
<i>with a meal of sheer technical perfection.</i>

843
01:24:30,052 --> 01:24:34,312
<i>A difficult choice between perfection
and heavenly delight.</i>

844
01:24:34,783 --> 01:24:38,745
<i>But, in true fairytale style,</i>

845
01:24:39,017 --> 01:24:40,691
<i>the heart wins out</i>

846
01:24:40,691 --> 01:24:45,112
<i>and tonight's award goes to the
"Pursuits of Heavenly Delight"!</i>

847
01:24:55,587 --> 01:24:57,150
Kiss me.

848
01:25:26,031 --> 01:25:28,192
<i>It must be the garam masala.</i>

849
01:25:28,785 --> 01:25:30,508
<i>Hold me back...</i>

850
01:26:16,989 --> 01:26:20,024
Slate 1, take 1.
"Love in a Wet Climate"

